name: Ramesh Bar & Restaurant

reviews.review_text:
One of the Gem of Goa. Best place to try local Goan food. Variety of Fish/prawns Thali they are serving at Rs.250/thali. Super tasty.
Go early to avoid rush. This place is quite crowded during lunch hour.
Must visit this place if u r roaming around Vasco/North Goa.
I love this place. Should be in ur bucket list.

One of the best local restaurants I‚Äôve been to! We tried the Chanak thali, Lepo thali, and prawns thali. The fish was super fresh and delicious. For starters, we had chicken chilly and squid masala. Definitely recommend this place!

Best fish fry available here. The freshness of fish offered here is unmatchable.
If you are okay with basic facilities, zero ambience and mainly want lip smacking Goan fish, this is the place to be.

We tried Modso masala fry, Lepo rawa fry, Tamso rawa fry. Their masala and freshness is the highlight.
Fish curry was awesome and Goa authentic style.

Its a narrow road (not busy though) and can be difficult to find Car parking. Alcohol is served. ü•≥

If you are anyway near this place during Goa visit, dont miss it.

Nestled in the heart of Corlim Ind. Estate, Ramesh Bar & Restaurant boasts an impressive rating of 4.4 from a remarkable 653 reviews. This cherished culinary spot is a must-visit for anyone craving authentic Goan fare, famous for its seafood offerings, with particular emphasis on the fantastic fish thali. With 31 mentions of "seafood" and 25 for "fish thali," it's clear that patrons are enamored with the richness of the ocean‚Äôs bounty served here.

The lighting is soft enough to lend a cozy feel, while the bustling lunch hours add a lively, communal vibe. However, it is advisable to arrive early to avoid the rush during lunch hours, as this hidden gem tends to fill rapidly with eager diners. While the facilities may be basic, the focus on delivering delicious food remains paramount, indeed a testament to the restaurant's commitment to quality over extravagance.

**Popularity & Reviews**

The overwhelming customer sentiment reflects genuine affection for this local eatery, with many customers mentioning it as a "bucket list" location while exploring the North Goa region.
